title: DON'T PUT THIS ON YOUR REGISTRY
text: I am a loyal Amazon customer I have been a Prime member for years and so when it was time for my now husband and I to make a registry for our wedding Amazon was an obvious option As I searched through all the options of things to put on the registry this popped up as a suggestion My husband and I both work multiple jobs and money is always tight so I figured if we were given this as a gift it would be a nice excuse to get away for a weekend Well it turns out if people contribute money towards this in your registry you don t actually get the gift cards You are just given credit to Amazon After email different people on messenger and different people on the phone I was told it is illegal to use group gifting contributions on Amazon for a gift card to something else When I said to the man this makes no sense why was this Massanutten gift card even an option then his response was well your guest got a pop up box explicitly explaining the federal laws I could be wrong but I think most times when we see a picture of a gift card and a title saying Massanutten Gift Card people think it is generally straight forward Well it s not br br Now if it is the case that all of this was because I had the group gifting tab checked to on then my question is why would amazon even allow that to be an option on gift cards to other places Needless to say the money my husband I and were going to use to take make step son snow tubing is now sitting in my Amazon credit balance and I am unable to use it for Massanutten br br I hope this helps someone else out there before they make the same mistake I did because let me tell you customer service will not help you

title: I hope Santa‚Äôs Sack works better than these bags.
text: Complete garbage I ordered of these little gift bags and the bags are a complete waste of time Here are the issues I have with them br The sticker with the barcode on them gets ripped in order to open the small plastic wrapping they come in So you have to do some digging to find out which is which if you ordered more than one as I did br It s very difficult to unfold the bags and it almost tears the paper trying to get them fully open br The small Velcro circle that keeps the bag closed clings harder to the other flap of Velcro than it does the adhesive it s supposed to be anchored with So when you open the bag you can t reseal it and you re left with a sticky circle where half of the Velcro closure should be br As you can see from the photo provided the handle comes off with very little effort Mine popped off while wrestling with the bag to open up br There is no denomination printed on the gift card itself br I bought gift bags with different amounts and aside from reviewing my purchase online I have no way to know which one is which br br I ended up removing the cards and putting them in my own bags to deliver the gift cards br br So for all of the above reasons I would not recommend these gift bags and wish I had stuck with the reindeer or snowflake gift card this year br Thanks for playing the part of the grinch this year Amazon Too bad your ubiquitous nature makes consumers of us all

title: Solution
text: Haha this is funny that I get to review my Amazon Gift Card So this is my re loadable gift card for all my Amazon purchases I don t know about anyone else but I hate all the little charges that come up on my account for Amazon It is nice that they don t charge till it ships but each product coming out one by one by one Sometimes it is confusing because I remember the full purchase of everything in my order and not the individual prices So I have to go back and look and see I have to be sure someone didn t get a hold of my card again it has happened in the past br br So here is a solution I found Just put one charge on my card for a gift card It gets loaded right to my account and I can reload it when I need to So no more little charges here and there adding up on my statement Easy So if that part of shopping with Amazon annoys you like it did me here is a solution that will keep you shopping happy I am just surprised that it is on my list of items to review It tickles me to see it here but hey maybe this will help someone else

title: Hidden Secret
text: I m not sure if this is known or not but you can set up a gift card to be your main payment here on Amazon set up refills with a credit card if it goes below a certain limit have your digital rewards for shipping and stuff come to that same gift card and skip having your credit card being a playground for price changes and rewards credit with Amazon br br I do my budget and the thing that frustrates me about stores and their price changes such as WM and Amazon is that I already calculated in my ledger for items when they do changes Then I have to go in and find which line it was on what was changed calculate the difference and create a new line item in my ledger It s annoying for me and I was burning through line after line every week Enter the gift card option for Amazon and I no longer need to worry about doing that It s kind of like a store credit except it s my money that I put on there And the fact that the company will put the rewards from shipping delay incentives on there and such is actually brilliant I think WM needs to follow suit with this philosophy Obviously keep an eye on the price changes to make sure they re not going the other way to some extent but it s way less of a headache to just let Amazon do Amazon in Amazon s gift card thing I love this idea and I think more companies need to follow suit

title: It was never delivered
text: I ordered a gift card for a friend s wedding gift It was a destination wedding and I wasn t attending in person but based on the expected delivery date it should have arrived before she left so I was ok with that I just found out after chatting with her a month later that she never received the gift She contacted amazon as it was on her registry as purchased and was transferred a couple of times As the purchaser I contacted amazon to request a refund and have them re issue a card and expedite shipping They said sure just go ahead and order the new one and I will refund your account right after That made no sense to me but I was going to do it until going through the process I realized I needed to change the shipping address Now I m really angry because I have to look up the darn address again Seconds later I was told I can t issue the refund because it has to go through the gift card blah blah blah department and I would get a call back on Monday At this point I m irate and asked to speak to a supervisor After a long hold I was told the supervisor approved a refund now but I can still go ahead and reorder My response is that I m not reordering anything until I get evidence that a refund is going to my credit card This was an awful experience and I don t trust ordering gift cards from amazon again I don t know what carrier was used but whatever disconnect happened between the shipping of the gift card and the delivery is not my problem I m also disappointed that Amazon has no controls in place that would show an order has been in transit for so long I should have noticed as well but I m the customer and I want my ordering experience to be seamless br br Update my friend told me that someone drove to her home in their personal vehicle and hand delivered the gift card to her on Sunday which was the day after I complained That was a good move but I m still very disappointed in this service

title: Do Not Use To Buy A Gift For A Friend Who Lives Overseas
text: I thought it would be a fun gift for my ex college roommate We share the same taste in music NOT NOT NOT If you buy it from the US and send the PIN overseas they won t honor it Amazon says nothing about it but when you get the card and your friend enters the PIN Spotify will not accept it Then you read the fine print on the card and there it is only you have to buy the card to get that part of the fine print Even worse I can t use the card for my own account because I have a family plan This has been a two day dumpster fire so far I gave it stars because the one star reviews seem to be written by bots most of the time But really it s a zero star deal if you want to give a gift to an overseas friend br br Note I love Spotify itself which is why I wanted to share it I cannot understand why they make it so hard to give as a gift I didn t want to go to Amazon or Target to buy it I wanted to give my money to Spotify itself but they are strangely obtuse about this simple thing br br EDIT When I contacted them Amazon called me back immediately and agreed with me that the posted information was misleading In spite of the no refunds warning they reimbursed me that same day Excellent customer service

title: Extremely convenient-- apparently out of necessity
text: Amazon makes it so easy to reload gift cards but it doesn t really make up for their horrendous gift card policy in the first place They should have an option to just use one gift card at a time instead of lumping them all together and forcing you to use them all at once or else use none of them at all I suppose I can see where this might be convenient to some but for the general population please make our lives a little easier and give us the option to separate out our gift cards Almost every other website is smart enough to let people do this Why not Amazon br br Reloading my gift card balance has been the only workaround I ve found to this issue so far but at least it works like a dream I try to keep my gift cards untouched unless I m purchasing digital media like movies or ebooks since it helps me set an internal budget on my Amazon sourced entertainment This way is fast and easy and lets me sort of handle my gift card spending so that I can spend part or all of my balance on various purchases Of course the main problem still exists but in lieu of a solution to that this is a fairly simple way to bypass the issues it causes

title: Gift cards are terribly delayed at least half the time; terrible customer service from Amazon
text: I have three grandkids with birthdays in April July and September that I like to give gift cards to But this year of the three gift cards ordered on April and September have not arrived on time even though they were ordered on time and with delivery dates well before the birthdays This has resulted in upsetting my grandkids and me a lot You should not promise to deliver simple items like gift cards if you cannot manage to deliver them on time This is terrible service from a world renowned company br Furthermore when I had contacted Amazon about the delayed gift card in April the associate I chatted with told me that they will not charge me for the gift card since it was not delivered on time and that it will be free of cost but then Amazon proceeded to cancel the gift card My grandchild tried using the gift card only to find that it was cancelled and was terribly upset understandably so The associate simply lied to me last time and told me that the gift card would be free of cost due to the delay I spend a lot of money on Amazon gift cards every year but I will be left with no choice but to stop using Amazon altogether and look for other vendors due to this abysmal service br br The final straw was the gift card ordered on September which Amazon says has been already fulfilled and claimed even though they also say that it has not even been delivered and the tracking confirms it br br I was planning to send another Amazon gift card for a substantial amount for someone else now but given the fact that the gift card that was supposed to be delivered on Monday has still not been delivered by Thursday I am going to have to find an alternative way There have been no efforts whatsoever on Amazon s part to fix the problem and empty words of apology every time I contact Amazon are just not enough to make amends for upsetting my grandkids

title: Not a traditional gift card, but there is a solution if you have a Family Plan and want to use it
text: It is unlikely that anyone will read reviews on a gift card but I am writing this review just in case Amazon identifies this as a gift card and treats it as such for the purposes of their refund return policy Further it is located in the gift card section of the site Despite this as other reviewers have stated this is not a true gift card By that I mean that it is not simply applicable to your account In order to get the benefit of this card you have to get in touch with Spotify customer service and have them assist you with a workaround their term Customer service can assist you with cancelling your account it may be possible to do this solution yourself You will then be able to upgrade to Premium and apply this card They will then walk you through further upgrading to a Family account and you can then invite your family members again with no loss of playlists At that point you will have been given credit for the amount and will have your next payment for the Family Plan due in about six months However I had to spend substantial time in Spotify s chat no phone number that I could find to get to this solution The first thing suggested by Customer Service was as follows What I would recommend is for you to request for a refund on your card or gift it to a special person that hasn t had Premium with us or someone with just a regular Premium plan or have a friend take it off your hands by purchase An absurd suggestion in my opinion It was only after I persistently sought other options that I was given the solution I detailed above Some might say that it is possible that the Customer Service script is to attempt to discourage you from using this solution first before giving you satisfaction in the hopes that some card holders will simply give up Some reviewers were able to get a refund from Amazon but I was not given this option

title: Buyer beware of thieves when registering card online, zero balance suprise
text: When you get your gift card you are encouraged to register it on the website on the back of the card in this case it was GiftCardMall Very shortly after registering the card on the site it then showed the balance ZERO That registration site either has a dishonest employee taking information as forms are submitted or there could be malware on their server siphoning card information br br You can call the number on the back of the card to report the fraud and customer service company Blackhawk Network who has poor reviews online will tell you the name of the company that stole your funds but you then have to fill out a dispute form and email it to them and then in days which has become over a month they are supposed to give you a new card A very inconvenient gift For safety if you get one of these cards use it up immediately or better yet move it to your Amazon gift card balance for safe keeping br br UPDATE almost weeks has gone by and the issue is has still not been resolved by the gift card company Blackhawk Network After several long annoying calls to them they say that Covid has slowed down their responses And they acknowledged there is theft happening on their registration sites how it is allowed to continue without being fixed is mind boggling Every couple weeks they will send out an email asking for copies of the same documents proof of purchase even if you already sent them in several times prior This is a complete failure of customer service br br Suggestion Rethink this stressful risky gift find a different gift card company that is more reliable for customer service Your safest bet is an Amazon gift card since they have the best customer service teams

title: Great Gift
text: This is a great gift idea for someone to splurge on some healthy and tasty food Our local Whole Foods in Connecticut has a short order station where you can get delicious hamburgers hot dogs sweet potato friends and shakes to eat in the store at a reasonable price There s a great soup salad and entree section and pizza dispensary too On Wednesdays you can buy one soup and get the other at discount It s an adventure shopping at Whole Foods These gift cards are a great gift to give someone a quality shopping and eating experience rather than just more stuff for their home

title: Like This Gift Card Option
text: Love to get and give gift cards to favorite eateries as it compels you to go out We like Paneras soups and sandwiches The tomato and broccoli and cheese soup are our favorites This is a pleasant eatery for a light and quick meal which is healthier than most fast food Love to give these to family members as sometimes they invite you along to enjoy the card with them It s great that Amazon has so many choices like this restaurant among their gift card selections When family and friends have enough stuff giving a gift card for an experience like this makes a thoughtful gift

title: Love Gift Cards to This Restaurant

text: I buy from Amazon for the convenience the good prices and mostly the peace of mind offered should there be a problem with the order This however does not extend to Gift Cards I purchased many of these over time and most times it went without any problem However when there is a problem Amazon s care free customer centric approach does not apply Here is a specific example I received an envelop with just the purchase receipt and no gift card I called immediately Customer Service and they told me they couldn t resolve this issue since the Gift Card was already used After a very long and frustrating hour long conversation I was offered the option to contact my bank and dispute the charge I will try this and follow up on how this issue is resolved At any rate I will stop purchasing these Gift Cards from Amazon as I don t want to go through this again I will instead buy them from the supermarket same price same product minus the convenience of free delivery

title: Convenient and fast - allows single purchases from multiple funding sources
text: For the way I purchase this gift card reload feature is a major convenience I have multiple sources of cards and sometimes want to use two to three to make a single purchase The ability to use a gift card comes in handy in those situations so being able to reload meets my needs perfectly br br The way I use it for multiple cards is to reload from one card then another until I have distributed the funding sources It literally takes seconds per reload and when I am using three or more cards it can all be done in a minute or two Then when I need to make a purchase the entire amount is waiting This is much faster and more efficient than purchasing multiple gift cards br br You can also have your gift card balance automatically reloaded from a single funding source when the balance hits a low mark I have not used that feature but can see how convenient it would be for some folks who use gift cards the way I do
